Here is the thing... on a total cold night, In the middle of this fast going (progreso) city is this famous churros place. So, we went to experience a Total Cuban Churro Shop... Allow me to explain, long lines, customized attitude, can't get the food you came here for. And as I write this, we are still waiting to be called. Might take another 15 more mins. So, at the end you will need to choose between a delicious churro and or a horrible customer service. Lucky for you, they do UberEats so you wont have to be barked at by the staff. Bottom line: bring a pound of patience, add a spoon of international culture interaction and top it with a happy tummy.  ;)
